A high-powered government delegation, led by the KwaZulu-Natal Premier, has met with farmers to quell tensions in Newcastle. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Police have arrested a suspect in connection with the double murder of Glen and Vida Rafferty. The pair were killed on their farm in Normandien last month. The suspects ransacked their home before fleeing with their vehicle. This arrest comes just hours after a high-powered government delegation, led by the KwaZulu-Natal Premier, met with farmers to quell tensions in Newcastle.